  1. Redo Question 11 in Assignment 7 using map.
quick.visual <- function(df, k) {
  stopifnot(k %in% c(1, 2, 3))
  
  categ.names <- df %>% 
    select_if(funs(is.character(.) & (length(unique(.)) < 4))) %>% 
    names()
  
  numeric.names <- df %>% 
    select_if(is.numeric) %>% 
    names()
  
  if (k == 1) {
    map(categ.names, function (x) map(categ.names, function(y)
      ggplot(df, aes_string(x, fill = y)) + geom_bar()))
    } else if (k == 2) {
      map(numeric.names, function (x) ggplot(df, aes_string(x)) + geom_density())
      } else {
    map(numeric.names, function (x) map(categ.names, function(y)
      ggplot(df, aes_string(x, col = y)) + geom_density()))
  }
}

titanic %>% 
  mutate(Pclass = as.character(Pclass), Survived = as.character(Survived)) %>% 
  quick.visual(k = 3)

  1. Write a function, using map, to • input: a data frame • output: a data frame of consist three columns x1, x2 and r where the pairs (x1, x2) are all possible pairs of continuous variables of the input data frame and r is the corresponding r square of x1 and x2. Test the function on the titanic data assuming that the PassengerID is also a continuous variable.
correlation.list <- function(df) {
  
  vars <- df %>% 
    select_if(is.numeric)
  
   len <-  length(vars)
   
  suppressWarnings(map_df(1:(len - 1), function(x) map_df((x + 1):len, function(y) data.frame(var1 = names(vars)[x],
                                                                     var2 = names(vars)[y],
                                                      r2 = round(summary(lm(vars[[y]] ~ vars[[x]]))$r.square, 4)))))
  
}

titanic %>% 
  correlation.list()
